author: Matt Lombardo | For NJ Advance Media
title: WATCH: Josh Huff flips into end zone for Eagles touchdown vs. New Orleans Saints
text:
Comments The 41-yard TD was nice enough. But that Josh Huff front flip into the end zone? Mercy. #NOvsPHI http://t.co/SDoVwTRScY â€” NFL (@NFL) October 11, 2015 
PHILADELPHIA -- Eagles wide receiver Josh Huff made sure that his first receiving touchdown was a memorable one. 
The second-year receiver hauled in a 41-yard Sam Bradford touchdown pass in the second quarter of Sunday's game against the New Orleans Saints at Lincoln Financial Field and capped the catch and run with a front-flip into the end zone, knotting the game up at 7-7. 
You can watch video of the touchdown above.
